President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation declaring May 7th to May 13th, 2017 as Public Service Recognition Week. The proclamation expresses gratitude for civil servants and acknowledges their daily efforts in keeping the government functioning and making the nation exceptional. President Trump emphasizes the importance of empowering civil servants to better help others, as well as the need for the government to operate more efficiently and securely. The proclamation calls upon Americans and all government agencies to recognize the dedication of public servants and observe the week through appropriate programs and activities.